---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro'
import ProjectMetaBar from '../../components/ProjectMetaBar.astro'
import SkillBadge from '../../components/SkillBadge.astro'

const stack = ['Django', 'HTMX', 'Alpine.js', 'PostgreSQL', 'pgvector', 'Pydantic', 'Docker', 'Coolify']
const metaItems = [
  { label: 'Type', value: 'Architecture template' },
  { label: 'Role', value: 'Designer & sole author' },
  { label: 'Repository', value: 'Private · available on request' },
  { label: 'Built on it', value: 'Almaeng · SportsIQ' },
]
---

<Base title="DAEMON-ONE | Wonsub Song (Tony)" lang="en" description="DAEMON-ONE: a deliberate Django architecture template. Modular Monolith, HTMX+SSR, Vertical Slicing, PostgreSQL-First.">
  <a href="/portfolio" class="text-sm hover:text-white transition-colors mb-8 inline-block" style="color:#8b949e;">
    ← Portfolio
  </a>

  <header class="mb-12">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">DAEMON-ONE</h1>
      <span style="font-size:0.75rem;padding:0.2rem 0.5rem;border-radius:4px;background:#0a1628;color:#60a5fa;border:1px solid #1e3a5f;font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.04em;">
        ARCH
      </span>
    </div>
    <p class="text-lg mb-2" style="color:#a1a1aa;">
      A Django architecture template built to eliminate structural drift across projects — deliberate tradeoffs, not a boilerplate.
    </p>
    <p class="text-sm mb-6" style="color:#52525b;">
      Private repository · Available on request
    </p>
    <ProjectMetaBar items={metaItems} />
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      {stack.map(s => <SkillBadge name={s} />)}
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="space-y-12" style="color:#a1a1aa;">
    <section>
      <h2 class="case-label">Why It Exists</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        After 15+ side projects, the same structural problems kept reappearing: business logic scattered
        across views and signals, unclear domain boundaries, and every project starting from scratch with
        the same mistakes. DAEMON-ONE is the architecture I designed to fix that — a structured Django
        monolith template with deliberate decisions built in from the start.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="case-label">Key Decisions</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-5 text-sm">
        <li>
          <p style="color:#e6edf3;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Modular Monolith over microservices</p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">Single deployable unit. Domain boundaries enforced via <code>interface.py</code> — the only file through which one domain can reach another. No cross-domain foreign keys. Complexity lives at the right boundary.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p style="color:#e6edf3;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">HTMX + SSR over React</p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">Server-driven UI state. No JS build step. LCP-first rendering by default. Alpine.js handles isolated client state only. The result: a full-stack product without a frontend build pipeline.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p style="color:#e6edf3;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">Vertical Slicing</p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">Logic, template, and style colocated per feature. Delete a folder and the feature is completely gone — no orphaned imports or lingering references. This also makes AI-assisted development tractable: scope the AI to one folder at a time.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p style="color:#e6edf3;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:0.3rem;">PostgreSQL-First</p>
          <p class="leading-relaxed">pgvector for semantic search, pgmq as message queue (replacing Redis), pg_search for full-text. One database, one deployment unit. No Redis or Elasticsearch complexity until the scale actually demands it.</p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="case-label">Architecture</h2>

      <p class="diag-sub">Folder Structure</p>
<pre class="tree-block">backend/domains/
├── <span class="th">accounts/</span>
│   ├── <span class="th">state/</span>             <span class="tc">← DB Owner · models · migrations · admin</span>
│   │   └── <span class="tk">interface.py</span>   <span class="ta">← only cross-domain exit</span>
│   ├── <span class="th">logic/</span>             <span class="tc">← Stateless · pure functions · Pydantic (frozen)</span>
│   └── <span class="th">pages/</span>             <span class="tc">← UI Slices · view + template colocated</span>
│       └── profile/
│           ├── views.py
│           └── profile.html
└── <span class="th">core/</span>                <span class="tc">← home · health · base models</span></pre>

      <p class="diag-sub" style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Request Flow</p>
      <div class="flow-col">
        <div class="flow-row">
          <div class="flow-box fb-blue">HTTP Request</div>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-edge">↓</div>
        <div class="flow-row">
          <div class="flow-box fb-gray">pages/views.py</div>
          <span class="flow-hint">thin handler</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-edge">↓</div>
        <div class="flow-row">
          <div class="flow-box fb-yellow">state/interface.py</div>
          <span class="flow-hint">only cross-domain boundary</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-edge">↓</div>
        <div class="flow-row">
          <div class="flow-box fb-gray">logic/services.py</div>
          <span class="flow-hint">pure functions · Pydantic in/out · no DB access</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-edge">↓</div>
        <div class="flow-row">
          <div class="flow-box fb-gray">state/models.py</div>
          <span class="flow-hint">Django ORM · django-lifecycle hooks</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flow-edge">↓</div>
        <div class="flow-row">
          <div class="flow-box fb-green">PostgreSQL</div>
          <span class="flow-hint">pgvector · pgmq · pg_search</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="case-label">Template Assessment</h2>
      <div class="assess-grid text-sm">
        <div class="assess-item">
          <p class="assess-score">80%</p>
          <p class="assess-label">Efficiency</p>
          <p class="assess-desc">One-command init, auto-domain discovery, full CI/CD pipeline wired.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="assess-item">
          <p class="assess-score">90%</p>
          <p class="assess-label">Effectiveness</p>
          <p class="assess-desc">Auth, AI integration, hybrid search, background jobs, smoke-tested deploys — production-grade out of the box.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-sm" style="margin-top:1rem;">
        CI pipeline: <code>pytest</code> → <code>smoke-test</code> (real PostgreSQL, health check) → <code>GHCR build+push</code>.
        The Docker image is never published if smoke fails — catches "tests pass but prod breaks" before it ships.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="case-label">Related Writing</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>→ <a href="/blog/modular-monolith-vs-microservice-en" style="color:#facc15;" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Modular Monolith vs Microservice — Why I Start with the Monolith</a></li>
        <li>→ <a href="/blog/vertical-slice-en" style="color:#facc15;" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Why I Prefer Vertical Slice Architecture</a></li>
        <li>→ <a href="/blog/why-i-did-not-pick-react-for-django-en" style="color:#facc15;" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Why I Chose HTML, CSS, and HTMX Over React for Django</a></li>
        <li>→ <a href="/blog/postgres-first-architecture-en" style="color:#facc15;" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">PostgreSQL-First Architecture: You Can Go Far Without Redis</a></li>
        <li>→ <a href="/blog/django-interface-py-domain-boundary-en" style="color:#facc15;" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Django Domain Boundaries: Why I Force an interface.py</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="case-label">Built On DAEMON-ONE</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <li>→ <a href="/portfolio/almaeng" style="color:#facc15;" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">Almaeng</a> — AI supplement analysis service, live in production</li>
        <li>→ <a href="/portfolio/kinetiq" style="color:#facc15;" class="hover:text-white transition-colors">SportsIQ</a> — Sports knowledge platform, in development</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="case-label">Status</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed">
        Private repository. The architecture evolves with each project built on it.
        Available on request.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .case-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #52525b;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  code {
    font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace;
    font-size: 0.82em;
    color: #facc15;
    background: rgba(250,204,21,0.06);
    padding: 0.1em 0.35em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }
  .assess-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 0.75rem; }
  .assess-item { padding: 0.9rem 1rem; border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border-radius: 6px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.01); }
  .assess-score { font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 700; font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace; color: #facc15; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 0.2rem; }
  .assess-label { font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #52525b; margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .assess-desc { font-size: 0.8rem; line-height: 1.55; color: #8b949e; }
  @media (max-width: 480px) { .assess-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

  /* diagram shared */
  .diag-sub { font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: #52525b; margin-bottom: 0.65rem; font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace; }
  .tree-block { font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace; font-size: 0.77rem; line-height: 1.75; color: #8b949e; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border-radius: 6px; padding: 1rem 1.2rem; overflow-x: auto; white-space: pre; }
  .th { color: #e6edf3; }
  .tk { color: #facc15; }
  .tc { color: #52525b; }
  .ta { color: rgba(250,204,21,0.65); }
  .flow-col { display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
  .flow-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.7rem; }
  .flow-box { font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace; font-size: 0.79rem; padding: 0.38rem 0.85rem; border-radius: 5px; border: 1px solid; white-space: nowrap; }
  .fb-blue  { color: #60a5fa; border-color: rgba(96,165,250,0.25);  background: rgba(96,165,250,0.05); }
  .fb-gray  { color: #e6edf3; border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.1);  background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02); }
  .fb-yellow{ color: #facc15; border-color: rgba(250,204,21,0.25);  background: rgba(250,204,21,0.04); }
  .fb-green { color: #3fb950; border-color: rgba(63,185,80,0.25);   background: rgba(63,185,80,0.04); }
  .flow-edge { color: rgba(250,204,21,0.28); font-size: 0.75rem; font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace; margin: 0.18rem 0 0.18rem 1.1rem; }
  .flow-hint { font-size: 0.71rem; color: #52525b; font-family: "JetBrains Mono", monospace; }
  @media (max-width: 640px) { .flow-hint { display: none; } .tree-block { font-size: 0.7rem; padding: 0.75rem 0.9rem; } }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .mb-12 { margin-bottom: 2.25rem; }
    .text-3xl { font-size: 1.75rem; line-height: 1.2; }
    .text-lg { font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.65; }
    .space-y-12 > :not([hidden]) ~ :not([hidden]) { margin-top: 2.2rem; }
    .leading-relaxed { line-height: 1.75; }
  }
</style>
